# Wiki toolchain and CI parity

- **Authoritative order.** **`make wiki-ci`** is the hard merge gate for compile plus Markdown, templates, frontend, strict external links, human readiness, and ingest queue health. **`.github/workflows/ci.yml`** runs **`make wiki-test`** then **`make wiki-ci`** then **`make wiki-quality-gate`**.
- **Pytest parity.** **`make wiki-test`** uses the first **`pytest`** on **`PATH`**. CI installs **`requirements.txt`** before that step. When your shell **`pytest`** is older than that pin, use **`.venv`**, **`pip install -r requirements.txt`**, and **`PATH=".venv/bin:$PATH"`** for **`make wiki-test`** or **`make wiki-all`**. Do not pass extra **`make`** goals after **`make wiki-test`** (**`make wiki-test -q`** is invalid). **README.md** (Pre-push and **Assistant preamble → repo mechanics** table), **`proposed/README.md`**, **`schema/wiki-quickstart.md`**, **`schema/karpathy-llm-wiki-bridge.md`** (**Pytest leg**), **`schema/AGENTS.md`** (githooks bullet), **`prompts/wiki-edit.txt`**, **`prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`**, **`prompts/ingest.txt`**, **`scripts/githooks/README.md`**, **`Makefile`** (top-of-file comments), **`.github/workflows/ci.yml`** (comment near **`make wiki-test`**), **`.github/pull_request_template.md`** (Verification **Pytest and CI** checkbox), **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`** (**Evidence** pytest paragraph), **`tests/test_pipeline_step_order.py`** (**`test_makefile_help_wiki_test_echo_warns_no_extra_make_goals`**), **`tests/test_karpathy_bridge_docs.py`** (**`test_readme_pre_push_links_toolchain_issue_template`**), and **`tests/test_githooks_wiring.py`** (**`test_githooks_readme_documents_modes`**) spell out the same pattern. Bump those together when **`requirements.txt`** changes the **`pytest`** pin.
- **Wiki Manager.** Edits to **`Makefile`** **`wiki-manager-*`** targets, **`scripts/wiki_manager_fork_delta.py`**, **`scripts/fork_delta_report.py`** (**`COMPARE=`**), **`ai/schema/wiki_manager_registry.v1.json`**, **`schema/wiki-manager.md`** (**## Machine-first repository (LLM Wiki Manager)**, **`## Canonical development hub`**, **`## Regression tests`** map), or **`schema/AGENTS.md`** (**`fork_delta_report.py`** and **`wiki_manager_fork_delta.py`** bullets) should stay aligned with **`README.md`** (opening **LLM Wiki Manager** graph, **Governance**, **Machine-first `wiki/`** section, Assistant preamble table), **`schema/wiki-quickstart.md`** (optional **`wiki-manager.md`** paragraph), **`schema/fork-sync.md`** (**LLM Wiki Manager as canonical toolchain home**), **`.github/pull_request_template.md`**, **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`** (Evidence list), **`tests/test_wiki_manager_fork_delta.py`**, **`tests/test_fork_delta_report.py`**, and **`tests/test_make_fork_delta_compare.py`**.
- **Typography globs.** **`scripts/validate_human_text.py`** defines **`MD_GLOBS`** for a narrow **`wiki/`** slice on **LLM Wiki Manager** (**`wiki/main.md`**, **`wiki/_templates/`**, **`wiki/sources/`**, **`wiki/synthesis/`** only). Changing globs requires **`schema/AGENTS.md`** bullet text, **`schema/fork-sync.md`** typography glob parity wording, **`tests/test_human_text_rules.py`**, and **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`** Evidence list to stay aligned. The same script rejects semicolons in scanned prose via **`_violations_from_prose_segment`** (ASCII **U+003B** and fullwidth **U+FF1B**).
- **lint_wiki citation heuristic.** Edits to **`scripts/lint_wiki.py`** (**`citation_heuristic_messages`**, skip rules) should stay aligned with **`schema/karpathy-llm-wiki-bridge.md`** subsection **Operator synthesis and `lint_wiki.py` claim bullets**, **`tests/test_lint_wiki.py`**, and **`wiki/synthesis/llm-wiki-family-repositories.md`** (tables for operator maps). **`README.md`** **Machine-first `wiki/`** and **`schema/AGENTS.md`** **`lint_wiki.py`** bullet echo the same story.
- **Git media policy.** **`.gitignore`** root **`llm_wiki_*`** raster globs, optional **`wiki/synthesis/hub-index.md`** (**`make wiki-hub`** output in this scaffold), and **`.gitattributes`** **`*.png`** / **`*.jpg`** / **`*.jpeg`** **`binary`** lines should stay aligned with **`README.md`** Pre-push, **`schema/wiki-quickstart.md`** (**Screenshots at repo root**, optional hub rollup, **Operator note** for **index drift** versus **HEAD** after **`make wiki-hub`**), **`SECURITY.md`** (**Root screenshots**), **`prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`** and **`prompts/ingest.txt`** (**Root screenshots** guidance), **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`**, and **`tests/test_karpathy_bridge_docs.py`** (**`test_gitignore_excludes_root_llm_wiki_media_globs`**, **`test_gitignore_excludes_optional_hub_index_rollup`**, **`test_gitattributes_marks_raster_images_binary`**, **`test_security_md_warns_query_artifact_path`**).
- **When changing step order or scripts** touched by the authoring prompt, update **`tests/test_pipeline_step_order.py`** and keep **`schema/AGENTS.md`**, **`README.md`**, **`schema/wiki-quickstart.md`**, **`prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`**, and **`Makefile`** wording consistent (the test enforces alignment).
- **Autopilot and daemon.** Forward **`VALIDATE_WIKI_ARGS`** like **`make`**. Use **`--ci-parity`** when soft failures should hard-fail like **`make wiki-ci`**. **`wiki_paths.AUTOPILOT_SOFT_FAILURE_STDERR_NOTICE`** is the single literal substring for soft-failure **stderr** detection. **`autopilot.py`** prints it (with a prefix). **`daemon.py`** repeats a short **stderr** hint when the captured autopilot **stderr** contains that substring and **`rc`** is still **0**. Heartbeat **`err`** uses **`autopilot_daemon_stderr_tail_chars()`** (floors at **`AUTOPILOT_DAEMON_STDERR_TAIL_MIN`** in **`wiki_paths.py`**) so tiny **`AUTOPILOT_LOG_TAIL_CHARS`** cannot hide the notice. See **`README.md`** (Autopilot versus CI), **`schema/AGENTS.md`** (**`wiki_paths.py`** helpers).
- **Filing issues.** Use **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`** on GitHub when you need a checklist for CI or **`Makefile`** drift before opening a PR (**Evidence** lists **`.gitignore`** drift including **`make wiki-hub`** / **`wiki/synthesis/hub-index.md`** on **LLM Wiki Manager**). **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml`** keeps blank issues enabled when that form does not fit.
- **Optional pre-push hooks.** **`scripts/githooks/pre-push`** runs **`make`** gates before **`git push`** when **`git config core.hooksPath scripts/githooks`** is set from the repo root. Changing **`WIKI_PRE_PUSH`** modes or which **`make`** target runs should stay aligned with **`scripts/githooks/README.md`**, **README.md** (**Assistant preamble → repo mechanics**), **`schema/AGENTS.md`**, **`.github/pull_request_template.md`**, **`Makefile`** **`make help`**, **`tests/test_githooks_wiring.py`**, **`tests/test_pipeline_step_order.py`**, and **`tests/test_karpathy_bridge_docs.py`**.
